msgctxt "#32223"
msgid "How to handle Hebrew end-of-sentence punctuation. Default 'reverse' moves trailing punct to the line start -- correct for Kodi setups that render source order without BiDi reorder (the observed default behaviour across Windows / Android / FENtastic). 'legacy' is the previous default (move leading punct to end) -- only use it if 'reverse' produces wrong output on your particular setup. 'off' disables the post-processor entirely."
